---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Paper Ledger"
  description="About Brickfielder and the ideas behind the site."
>
  <section class="landing-intro">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1 class="page-title">About</h1>
  </section>

  <section class="section prose-page">
    <p>
      "Brickfieder" is a nod to my long-standing passion for meteorology. A
      Brickfielder is a hot, dry, and dusty northwesterly wind that blows across
      southern Australia from the interior deserts during late spring and
      summer. I have always liked complex systems, and tried to understand them
      as much as possible.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
